{"id":"4388","name":"Bedtime","tagline":"Get a rundown of tomorrow.","icon":"ios13 c4271458815 g59649","latest":"14181","description":"\n\t\t\t\t\t<h1>Bedtime</h1>\n<p>Bedtime is a shortcut that focuses on preparing you for tomorrow without having to do a thing.</p>\n<h2>What does Bedtime do?</h2>\n<p>Bedtime will tell you tomorrow’s weather, check your calendar for the first event you have, and creates an alarm to wake you up in time for your first event.</p>\n<h2>Set-up</h2>\n<p>To set Bedtime up for you use, go to the second dictionary in the shortcut and answer the questions found in the comment before said dictionary. </p>\n<p>These answers will be used to make the shortcut more personalised as well as to ensure accurate creation of alarms.</p>\n<h2>How to use Bedtime</h2>\n<p>One option for activating the shortcuts is to have Bedtime in your Shortcuts widget list to easily set it off before bed.</p>\n<p>Another option is to create an Automation that sets it off at a specific time that you go to bed.</p>\n<h2>Alarms</h2>\n<p>This shortcut will use the estimated travel time to your first event, plus the approximate time you take to get ready in mornings, in order to create an alarm which will wake you at the perfect time.</p>\n<p>If the alarm would be after the time at which you would be awake anyway (without an alarm), it will not create an alarm, saving you from having a random alarm going off the next day.</p>\n<h3>Please note</h3>\n<p>Currently, the shortcut will not create an alarm for you if you have an alarm that is repeating on the day that is tomorrow, which is to say if you have an alarm repeating on Thursdays, this shortcut will not create an alarm when you run it on Wednesdays.</p>\n<p>If you set an alarm (which isn’t repeating) for tomorrow, the shortcut will ignore this and still create it’s own alarm.</p>\n\t\t\t\t","releasenotes":"<p><strong>1.0.0 - Jan. 24, 2020, 2:18 a.m.</strong></p>"}